Jul 30 2009 	A calm sanctuary in the heart of hectic London	My girlfriend and I stayed here for one night the other weekend. We had to attend a party in Mayfair and needed a place to lay our heads for the night. We arrived by taxi and were immediately provided assistance from a friendly doorman. The check-in was smooth and efficient and the receptionist was charming and friendly throughout the process. Our room was located overlooking the courtyard at the front of the hotel and there seemed something fitting and thoroughly British about the view of the surrounding townhouses of St. James and the large Union Jack fluttering above the entrance to the hotel. Our room was large and it was charmingly decorated, albeit in a clean and uncluttered manner. Rich, quality fabrics were used in the bedroom and the bathroom was clad in polished white marble. The bathtub was huge and also benefitted from a drench shower head. Furthermore, the hotel uses REN bathroom products, which happen to be our favorite.I needed some pressing done ahead of the party and this was promptly collected and swiftly returned, with the employee that conducted the interaction being charming and friendly. After a long, hectic night at the party it was great to return to Dukes. The hotel is nestled in such a location that the hustle and bustle of the metropolis and the cacophany of traffic noise on Piccadilly just disapated as we walked the quiet streets of St. James. By the time we reached Dukes we were surrounded by nothing but serene silence. This, coupled with the massive bed and soft linen, (and perhaps several bottles of wine consumed at the party) ensured we slept extremely well. Whilst we didn't have breakfast at the hotel we did enjoy a cup of tea in the small but pleasant hotel lobby. Sitting in the over-sized comfortable armchairs in the lobby, sipping hot Earl Gray tea and reading the Sunday paper with light streaming in through the huge sash windows was just the perfect and proper way to kickstart a Sunday. Dukes is a great little secret. Whilst it doesn't have the same presence as some of London's bigger hotels, it benefits from an amazing location in the heart of the city and is near Green Park, Buckingham Palace, Piccadilly Circus, Mayfair, Regent Street and Oxford Street. Everything you need is within a walk of the hotel. However, Dukes best strength is that whilst the hustle of London remains but a few short steps away, it feels a world away from the calm, comfortable and warm sanctuary of the hotel. It is fitting that such a jewel is located so close to Buckingham Palace!	
