Jan 17 2007 	Great locaction and tradition to match	We stayed here during the hottest part of the Summer of 06...despite those conditions, our room was comfortable without any excessive air conditioning noise. The location is exceptional for those who want to see and walk (or tube) to everything. The staff was very helpful and the bar was wonderful (it was the reason we booked The Dukes...it was Herb Caen's favorite bar in all of London...pricey but fun...a very interesting group of guests hanging out in the small but cozy sitting rooms...and cigars are not only permitted, they are sold on the premises! They do have a dress code, which I managed to violate our second day there. We waltzed into the bar after having walked all over the city in 90+ degree heat (fahrenheit you ninny)...I was in shorts (silk knee length but dressy, if you can say dressy shorts)...the head waiter discreetly told us to go upstairs to change....it may seem picky, but I think they will have to review their policy in light of the coming global warming. All in all, the Dukes was an experience that I had looked forward to for years, and I'm glad we stayed there...I don't know anything about the new owners..but there is definitely work to be done in the hotel...we had trouble with lights...I think it was related to fuses...and the elevator did not work the entire time we were there...but thank God, the freight lift worked...it just took longer. We only had one breakfast in the hotel, and as I recall the selection was more than adequate...the prices high (as expected) and the quality good.	
