Dec 23 2005	Quiet Very Clean Very Lovely Excellent Service Good Location	This hotel is expensive for the typical tourist, but if you absolutely require quiet and cleanliness, as well as atmospheric elegance, then this is worth the price. The hotel is in an incredibly quiet side street. There was virtually no street noise. There was also very little to no in-hotel noise; I only rarely heard a dull sound of someone's door opening or closing, and even though I was near the elevator, I never heard anyone using it. I was also never awakened by people talking or hallway noise. The rooms are tiny, but I found it plenty big enough for me (I was one person in a room; my travelling companion stayed in another room in another part of the hotel and loved her room also). The decor was very lovely. The room and bathroom were absolutely clean. I had not one complaint in this area. My bathroom was very tiny (smaller than my travelling companion's bathroom - the rooms and bathrooms are all different), but the size did not bother me. The tub was high off the ground, however, and a small step was built into an outside corner of the tub to step up into it, along with a rail to grab onto. I'm fairly young and physically fit, but I don't think an elderly or much less physically fit person would be entirely safe or comfortable maneuvering it. I would expect that anyone complaining would be moved to another room if available, but if you require ease of access to the tub, I would mention it when reserving, as I'm not sure how many rooms (if any others) have this particular set up. The other person I travelled with said that her bathtub had a lovely but ineffective glass half-tub length shower door that did not keep the entire bathroom from being doused with water when she used the shower. Luckily, the shower could be hand held so that she could sit in the tub to rinse without spraying down the entire room. These two small problems with our bathrooms were not show-stoppers, but probably should be addressed. The furniture is very nice - not junky hotel furniture, but the type of furniture you'd expect in the guest room of a friend with a lovely home. The linens are beautiful, and spotless - no qualms touching the bedspread, which in lesser hotels sometimes looks as though it hasn't been laundered between guests. There's none of that nonsense here. The bed and pillows are very comfortable. The service is first rate - every time you leave your room, it is tidied. I know there are some posts on here about robberies, and I was concerned about that also, but each room has a small safe and I felt completely secure leaving my valuables in it when I left the room. The staff at the desk were fabulous - every piece of information I asked for was supplied in a genuinely courteous and personable fashion, and they were always right. I thought it was funny that people were complaining about the cost of the breakfast until I experienced it myself. It is oddly frustrating to order a tiny meal (scrambled egg and toast) and be charged more than what a dinner in the same room had cost. I ordered what I thought was a fairly reasonably priced few items from the a la carte menu, but didn't understand that when I was offered to help myself to the buffet as well, that the waitress did not understand that I had ordered ala carte (which doesn't include the buffet or pastries). Therefore, the next morning I mentioned to the waitress that I hoped my and my travelling companion's breakfast wouldn't total 50 dollars again (!) and she explained about the ala cart pricing. So you have to indicate that that is how you are ordering. It's still pricey, but not heart stoppingly so. If you order toast, and instead they bring you a bunch of pastries with your toast, send the pastries back - that lovely basket of stuff you won't eat will cost a little fortune. For a lovely treat, have afternoon or evening tea in the drawing room. It's a beautiful addition to the hotel and the tea and cakes are delicious. We didn't drink in the bar - we were expecting some fabulous atmospheric bar, but to be honest, it was a fairly small, typical looking bar that you might find in a lot of places, and it was smokey as well. We had no desire to spend time in it, so can't attest to the fabulousness of the martinis. I would absolutely stay at this hotel again. The entire stay was wonderful.	
